    "long_instructions": "# Sensors / Data AI Assistant\r\n\r\n## Do This:\r\n- *Ask About Sensors*: Request information about which sensors might help solve the mystery and how they collect data\r\n- *Request Data Types*: Ask what types of data the sensors can provide and how that data might be useful.\r\n- *Seek Explanations*: If you’re not sure how a specific sensor works or why it’s useful, ask for a simple explanation.\r\n- *Propose Solutions*: Share your ideas for solving the problem, and ask the chatbot if your solution is feasible based on the data.\r\n- *Keep Learning*: Feel free to ask \"why\" or \"how\" questions to deepen your understanding of sensors and data\r\n\r\n\r\n**Example Prompts:**\r\n- How can I figure out what type of sensor to use for a problem in my scenario?\r\n- What sensors can measure environmental changes, like temperature or noise?\r\n- How can I use sound or light data to figure out what’s happening in my scenario?\r\n- Can you explain how a motion sensor works and what kind of data it collects?\r\n- What does a light sensor measure, and what do 'lux' and 'flicker frequency' mean?\r\n- How can I use data from multiple sensors to find patterns in my scenario?\r\n- What steps should I take to analyze sensor data and connect it to possible solutions?\r\n- How can I decide if my proposed solution is supported by the data I’ve collected?\r\n- What other factors might influence the data collected by my sensors?\r\n\r\n   ",
